OL,3,C"Our last chance at justice," says
OL,4,CPortsmouth woman given infected blood
OL,6,F"The evidence is out there now, and
OL,7,Fthey can no longer deny, deny, deny,
OL,8,Fand it will cost them (the
OL,9,Fgovernment). But then it's cost us our
OL,10,Flives. So what's money?"
OL,12,FJackie says whatever the outcome of
OL,13,Fthe Infected Blood Inquiry she will
OL,14,Fneed to stop campaigning.
OL,16,F"I need to be able to know that if
OL,17,Fanything happens to me, the funds are
OL,18,Fthere to pay for care for my daughter.
OL,19,FAnd I want to live a little bit of my
OL,20,Flife
